# Assets Investment Real Estate Property Adjustment Hedging Amount

## identifier
de5315

## type
float

## definition
Report the hedging adjustment required to translate the aggregate investment property balance to the effective post-derivatives position. 

A hedging adjustment represents the adjustment required to translate the effective exposure associated with hedging investments. The purpose of a hedging investment is to offset the risk of changes in the fair value or investment cash flows of another contract.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=debit
- name=Assets.Investment.RealEstateProperty.AdjustmentHedging.Amount
- classification=baf/bafpo/bafpo5.02.04
- period=instant
